06/03/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police detained seven people on Friday (March 4th) for disrupting public order during an anti-government rally in Zagreb. 
Thousands of protestors organised via Facebook gathered in the capital to call for the cabinet's resignation. 
At one point, protestors began banging on the car of government spokesman Mladen Pavic, who was not injured. 
(Hina, Poslovni Dnevnik, tportal.hr - 04/03/11)
